 Alliance of Five Eyes, an agreement to share information 

00:00:10.833 --> 00:00:16.086
 between the United States, the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia and New Zealand. 

00:00:22.760 --> 00:00:27.415
 During World War II Britain and the US shared information about the Nazis. 

00:00:27.416 --> 00:00:29.355
 They had an agreement called BRUSA, 

00:00:29.356 --> 00:00:31.372
 which allowed them to exchange staff, 

00:00:31.843 --> 00:00:35.359
 and both countries have set rules for handling secret information. 

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:37.957
 And this deal won them so much, 

00:00:37.958 --> 00:00:43.256
 that they used it after the war under the original name of the British-American Agreement. 

00:00:43.492 --> 00:00:46.990
 The agreement has expelled news agencies so much 

00:00:46.990 --> 00:00:50.718
 that they spread it to the other three peoples of the British Commonwealth - 

00:00:50.719 --> 00:00:53.336
 Canada, Australia and New Zealand. 

00:00:53.337 --> 00:00:56.062
 And here is the Alliance of Five Eyes. 

00:00:56.907 --> 00:01:01.460
 They were supposed to help share information about the Soviet Union and China, 

00:01:01.461 --> 00:01:04.581
 but the agreement has not been used for this purpose all the time. 

00:01:05.113 --> 00:01:07.805
 Five eyes created a system called Echelon. 

00:01:07.806 --> 00:01:10.674
 It is a system for sharing signal information. 

00:01:10.675 --> 00:01:14.927
 Echelon was a project to share bugged phone calls 

00:01:14.928 --> 00:01:19.176
 satellite information and fiber optic communication. 

00:01:19.297 --> 00:01:22.153
 The project was allegedly printed in 1971, 

00:01:22.154 --> 00:01:25.457
 developed as new technologies. 

00:01:25.799 --> 00:01:29.401
 Nobody is 100% sure who is the target and how often, 

00:01:29.835 --> 00:01:32.139
 because it is very secret. 

