 When politicians began to ask in 1992, 

00:01:35.857 --> 00:01:39.061
 Britain and the US refused to exist, 

00:01:39.062 --> 00:01:43.388
 and refuse to this day, even though Australia and New Zealand admit it. 

00:01:43.744 --> 00:01:50.554
 Today it is considered the ultimate global spy network capable of listening to every call 

00:01:50.555 --> 00:01:53.681
 or read every email around the world. 

00:01:59.656 --> 00:02:03.503
 We know that this system has existed since 2000, 

00:02:03.504 --> 00:02:10.792
 in 1997, a BBC documentary was broadcast by a man named Duncan Campbell, 

00:02:11.014 --> 00:02:14.736
 He had a source from this place in Menwith Hill, North Yorkshire. 

00:02:15.191 --> 00:02:21.250
 His work was part of the Echelon system in strange structures known as "Radoms." 

